  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the effects of exogenous selenium supplementation on autoimmune thyroiditis.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In patients with autoimmune thyroiditis， investigators compared changes in thyroid function,&#xD;
      anti-thyroid peroxidase antibody, anti-thyroglobulin antibody, thyroid magnetic resonance&#xD;
      T1-mapping values and metabolic indicatorsfrom baseline to the end of treatment (12 weeks)&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
